  "doc_id": "38809",
  "text": "We screened rice plants for herbivore-induced transcripts using rice microarrays and found that one WRKY TF, OsWRKY53, was up-regulated after SSB infestation . Through reverse transcription PCR, we obtained the full-length complementary DNA (cDNA) of OsWRKY53, which includes an open reading frame of 1,464 bp (Supplemental Fig.  S1 ). Phylogenetic analysis of the characterized group I-type WRKYs from different species revealed that OsWRKY53 is homologous to ZmWRKY33 in Zea mays , TaWRKY53-a and TaWRKY53-b in Triticum aestivum [CITATION_1] , NaWRKY6 in N. attenuata [CITATION_2] , and AtWRKY33 in Arabidopsis (Supplemental Fig. S1 ; [CITATION_3] , which share 69%, 67%, 64%, 51%, and 51% amino acid sequence identity with OsWRKY53, respectively.",
